# AutoLogReader PWA

A soft-pastel Progressive Web App that reads log files from the private `tel-auto` repo via GitHub API.

## Quick Setup

### 1. Edit `index.html` — fill in your credentials

Open `index.html` and find the `CONFIG` block near the top of the `<script>` section:

```js
const CONFIG = {
  owner:  'YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME',   // ← your GitHub username
  repo:   'tel-auto',
  branch: 'main',
  token:  'YOUR_PAT_TOKEN',         // ← your ghp_... token
};
```

Replace both values and save.

### 2. Push to a public GitHub repo

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "initial"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/tel-monitor.git
git push -u origin main
```

### 3. Enable GitHub Pages

Go to **Settings → Pages** → Source: `main` branch, `/(root)` folder.

Your app will be live at `https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/tel-monitor/`

---

## Adding New Log Files

To support a new `.log` file, add one entry to the `FILE_PARSERS` object in `index.html`:

```js
'newfile_debug.log': {
  label: '📄 New File',   // tab label
  color: 'mint',          // rose | sky | mint | lavender
  parse(raw) {
    return raw.trim().split('\n').reverse().map((line, i) => {
      const m = line.match(/your regex here/);
      if (!m) return null;
      return { id: i, datetime: m[1], field1: m[2], field2: m[3] };
    }).filter(Boolean);
  },
  columns: [
    { key: 'datetime', label: 'Date / Time', render: r => dtCell(r.datetime) },
    { key: 'field1',   label: 'Field 1',     render: r => esc(r.field1) },
    { key: 'field2',   label: 'Field 2',     render: r => esc(r.field2) },
  ],
  rowClass: () => '',   // return a CSS class string based on row data, or ''
},
```

That's it — the app auto-discovers files in the repo root and shows tabs only for files it has a parser for.

---

## PWA Icons

The `manifest.json` references `icon-192.png` and `icon-512.png`. Add square PNG icons to the repo root for best install experience. Without them the PWA still works but uses the browser default icon.

---

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `index.html` | Entire app — UI, parsers, GitHub API logic |
| `manifest.json` | PWA metadata (name, icons, theme) |
| `sw.js` | Service worker — caches app shell for offline use |
| `README.md` | This file |
